  "texts": [
    "These strategies, tailored to meet the specific needs and preferences of diverse users, can foster a sustained and appropriate trust in AI.",
    "While some individuals may place excessive trust in AI because of a high trust propensity, others, hindered by limited understanding of AI and a lower sense of self-efficacy, may demonstrate a lack of trust.",
    "Lockey et al. (2020) discovered a widespread desire among individuals to learn more about AI.",
    "Therefore, in developing trustworthy AI, it is crucial to acknowledge the varying levels of trust people have toward AI and to devise effective communication strategies, engaging in AI education to bridge this knowledge gap.",
    "Moreover, hedonic motivation plays a critical role in shaping trust in AI, with the potential to cause users to overtrust AI systems."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Lockey et al. (2020) discovered a widespread desire among individuals to learn more about AI."
  ]
